Download and install Apache Kafka
	0. Open a linux terminal
		For windows, install and open gitbash terminal (https://git-scm.com/downloads)
		
	1. Download and extract Kafka (https://kafka.apache.org/downloads)
	
	2. start zookeeper (https://manishankarjaiswal.medium.com/installing-and-running-apache-kafka-on-windows-a-step-by-step-guide-part-1-7e957942e841)
		.\bin\windows\zookeeper-server-start.bat .\config\zookeeper.properties
		
	3. start kafka (https://kafka.apache.org/quickstart)

		$ KAFKA_CLUSTER_ID="$(bin/kafka-storage.sh random-uuid)"		
		$ bin/kafka-storage.sh format --standalone -t $KAFKA_CLUSTER_ID -c config/server.properties	
		$ bin/kafka-server-start.sh config/server.properties
 